g.text: Click Finish when the download has completed. Check all
ECMs for stored DTCs and erase as necessary.
From the main menu, navigate to DOWNLOAD, then
Enter the password, then select Automatic Model Selection.
The password can be found on TriumphOnline.
Click Start. If the chassis ECM calibration is up to date, the diagnostic tool will
display a message at this point indicating that an update is NOT required.
Select the correct calibration for your region. Click Next.
Check the selected calibration is correct for your model and
Connect the Triumph Diagnostic Tool. Turn the ignition ON.
Make sure the engine Start/Stop switch is in the RUN (ON)
